*portage-2.1.3_rc6 (29 Jun 2007)

  29 Jun 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.3_rc6.ebuild:
  2.1.3_rc6 bump.  This fixes bugs #139600, #141550, #142473, #144333,
  #144440, #147558, #148514, #175891, #180706, #182786, #182964, #183167,
  and #183431.

*portage-2.1.3_rc5 (23 Jun 2007)

  23 Jun 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> +portage-2.1.3_rc5.ebuild:
  2.1.3_rc5 bump.  This fixes bugs #143340, #180165, #182428, and #182571.
  The "save_summary" and "echo" elog modules are now enabled by default.
  Setting PORTAGE_ELOG_SYSTEM in make.conf will override this, so if you
  don't want elog set PORTAGE_ELOG_SYSTEM="" in make.conf.

*portage-2.1.3_rc4 (17 Jun 2007)

  17 Jun 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> -portage-2.1.3_rc3.ebuild,
  +portage-2.1.3_rc4.ebuild:
  2.1.3_rc4 bump for bug #182346 (use device/inode numbers to determine
  file ownership during unmerge so that files are not accidentally
  unmerged due to path mismatch that can be caused by symlinks).

*portage-2.1.3_rc3 (15 Jun 2007)

  15 Jun 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> -portage-2.1.3_rc2.ebuild,
  +portage-2.1.3_rc3.ebuild:
  2.1.3_rc3 bump for bug #182157 (don't chmod 0 symlinks before unlink
  and don't aggressively unmerge symlinks to directories).

*portage-2.1.3_rc2 (15 Jun 2007)

  15 Jun 2007; Zac Medico <zmedico@gentoo.org> -portage-2.1.3_rc1.ebuild,
  +portage-2.1.3_rc2.ebuild:
  2.1.3_rc2 bump for bug #182105 (fix a traceback that is triggered at
  emerge exit if PROMPT_COMMAND is exported).

